Abstract = {{In this paper we analyze the effect of intrusion detection and response
   on the reliability of a cyber physical system (CPS) comprising sensors,
   actuators, control units, and physical objects for controlling and
   protecting a physical infrastructure. We develop a probability model
   based on stochastic Petri nets to describe the behavior of the CPS in
   the presence of both malicious nodes exhibiting a range of attacker
   behaviors, and an intrusion detection and response system (IDRS) for
